      "postNumber": 2,
      "createdAt": "2022-05-30T05:16:42.878Z",
      "author": "rob (Roberto Tremonti)",
      "cookedHtml": "<p>Hey <a class=\"mention\" href=\"/u/vlad723\">@Vlad723</a><br />\nThe Phone column doesn’t support it, but you can send a webhook when you change a column.</p><aside class=\"onebox allowlistedgeneric\">\n  <header class=\"source\">\n      <img src=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/monday/original/2X/5/519a715ac28cae0711aeabd44665963d0ee499d2.png\" class=\"site-icon\" width=\"152\" height=\"152\" />\n\n      <a href=\"https://support.monday.com/hc/en-us/articles/360003540679-Webhook-integration-\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Support</a>\n  </header>\n\n  <article class=\"onebox-body\">\n    <div class=\"aspect-image\"><img src=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/monday/optimized/1X/41f46e5e9ea124f10772b48bfbf05a8c96547b79_2_690x127.jpeg\" class=\"thumbnail\" width=\"690\" height=\"127\" /></div>\n\n<h3><a href=\"https://support.monday.com/hc/en-us/articles/360003540679-Webhook-integration-\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Webhook integration</a></h3>\n\n  <p>5 min read\n\n\nFeature\n\n\n \n\nmonday.com offers the ability to send a Webhook via our integrations, or you could even create them via the API. You can send a Webhook each time a chosen event occurs wit...</p>\n\n\n  </article>\n\n  <div class=\"onebox-metadata\">\n    \n    \n  </div>\n\n  <div></div>\n</aside>\n<p>\nThen, you can directly change the column or create a “Send Webhook” button that does it for you.</p>"
